
[1]ironflint

   I'RONFLINT, n. Ferruginous quartz; a subspecies of quartz, opake or
   translucent at the edges, with a fracture more or less conchoidal,
   shining and nearly vitreous. It is sometimes in very minute and perfect
   six-sided prisms, terminated at both extremities by six-sides pyramids.
   It occurs also in masses, and in small grains. Its varieties are red,
   yellow,and greenish.
